       In this chapter you will work through examples that teach
       you how to:

          +o Point, click, and drag using the mouse

          +o Select a window to make it active

          +o Move a window to a new position on the screen

          +o Change the size of a window

          +o Minimize a window into an icon

          +o Restore an icon back into a window

          +o Use the window menu

       Before you start, you must log into your computer.  Your
       system administrator should have created an account for you.

























