       1.1  IIIInnnnttttrrrroooodddduuuucccciiiinnnngggg tttthhhheeee MMMMoooottttiiiiffff WWWWiiiinnnnddddoooowwww MMMMaaaannnnaaaaggggeeeerrrr

       The Motif Window Manager (MWM) is a program that runs with
       the X Window System and helps you manage the windows on your
       screen.  MWM provides functions for opening, closing, mov-
       ing, and resizing windows.  It's MWM that displays the
       three-dimensional frame around each window.

       Without MWM, your windows would not have borders and it
       would be difficult, if not impossible, to perform many sim-
       ple window functions.

       1.1.1  SSSSttttaaaarrrrttttiiiinnnngggg tttthhhheeee WWWWiiiinnnnddddoooowwww MMMMaaaannnnaaaaggggeeeerrrr

       Your system administrator should have configured your
       account so that MWM starts automatically when you start X.
       Your account may also be configured so that X starts
       automatically when you log in.

       Since different computer systems have different ways of
       starting X and Motif, you should consult with your system
       administrator to learn how to get started.

       Start your Motif environment now.





























